00:13:56,844 --> 00:13:57,864
All good.

276
00:14:00,094 --> 00:14:01,734
Thank you for the candies, Fu.

277
00:14:03,804 --> 00:14:05,804
Oh, these are from you?

278
00:14:06,204 --> 00:14:07,264
Thank you.

279
00:14:10,454 --> 00:14:12,484
By the way...

280
00:14:13,444 --> 00:14:15,474
Where are all the grape-flavored ones?

281
00:14:15,544 --> 00:14:17,784
What a bummer. Those are the best ones.

282
00:14:23,424 --> 00:14:25,064
Ugh, nothing but the grape-flavored ones.

283
00:14:25,204 --> 00:14:26,004
What a bummer.

284
00:14:26,174 --> 00:14:27,854
I don't even get to eat the other flavors.

285
00:14:30,674 --> 00:14:32,104
Oops, sorry.

286
00:14:33,574 --> 00:14:34,574
Uh...

287
00:14:34,644 --> 00:14:36,814
If everything is done,

288
00:14:37,324 --> 00:14:38,124
this evening,

289
00:14:38,164 --> 00:14:41,154
I would like to treat you
to dinner as a thank-you.

290
00:14:42,224 --> 00:14:43,654
That sounds nice.

291
00:14:44,564 --> 00:14:46,824
You're still as adorable as ever, Fu.

292
00:14:47,444 --> 00:14:49,044
Anyway, excuse me

293
00:14:49,084 --> 00:14:51,404
while I take a shower and get dolled up nicely.

294
00:14:52,174 --> 00:14:53,174
Sure.

295
00:14:53,614 --> 00:14:56,244
Jang, please take care
of our dinner this evening.

296
00:14:56,284 --> 00:14:57,284
Of course.

297
00:14:57,744 --> 00:14:59,204
- Same place.
- Okay, got it.

298
00:15:22,604 --> 00:15:23,604
How have you been?

299
00:15:23,734 --> 00:15:24,734
Good?

300
00:15:25,674 --> 00:15:26,674
I've been good.

301
00:15:26,954 --> 00:15:27,954
Thank you.

302
00:15:28,574 --> 00:15:29,574
Here you go.

303
00:15:33,014 --> 00:15:35,214
Kluayhom, give this a try.

304
00:15:35,574 --> 00:15:36,644
This dish

305
00:15:36,684 --> 00:15:38,974
was specifically designed
for this place by the chef.

306
00:15:43,454 --> 00:15:45,084
Are you still into Moo?

307
00:15:45,744 --> 00:15:46,744
Mm...

308
00:15:47,924 --> 00:15:48,924
I would say.

309
00:15:51,934 --> 00:15:53,234
After this long?

310
00:15:54,274 --> 00:15:55,274
Mm.

311
00:15:56,304 --> 00:15:57,394
Well...

312
00:15:58,814 --> 00:16:00,654
But I guess
I'll have to try a little bit more.

313
00:16:01,204 --> 00:16:02,204
What else could I do?

314
00:16:02,314 --> 00:16:03,634
There's no stopping my heart now.

315
00:16:46,009 --> 00:16:47,449
So he likes the grape-flavored ones.

316
00:16:51,859 --> 00:16:52,859
Look at those hearts.

317
00:16:53,041 --> 00:16:55,161
- How many? One, two, three, four, five...
- Uh...

318
00:16:55,201 --> 00:16:56,321
Whoa, countless of them.

319
00:16:56,391 --> 00:16:57,391
Fu,

320
00:16:59,161 --> 00:17:00,391
my name is Kluayhom.

321
00:17:01,481 --> 00:17:02,871
Uh... here's for you.

322
00:17:02,981 --> 00:17:03,981
Hey, I have to go.

323
00:17:06,201 --> 00:17:07,771
Uh... thanks.

324
00:17:10,021 --> 00:17:11,021
Uh...

325
00:17:11,841 --> 00:17:12,611
Actually,

326
00:17:12,651 --> 00:17:13,981
I like you.

327
00:17:17,091 --> 00:17:18,571
Actually,

328
00:17:18,921 --> 00:17:20,841
I'm allergic to certain artificial sweeteners,

329
00:17:20,941 --> 00:17:22,011
including...

330
00:17:23,501 --> 00:17:24,891
the one used in this candy.

331
00:17:25,091 --> 00:17:26,271
I can't eat it.

332
00:17:26,311 --> 00:17:27,741
Thank you, anyway.

333
00:17:28,271 --> 00:17:29,271
Sure.

334
00:17:33,591 --> 00:17:34,741
There's also some cake.

335
00:17:37,111 --> 00:17:38,551
Then, I should get going.

336
00:18:13,513 --> 00:18:16,103
No matter how many years,
you always look elsewhere.

337
00:18:16,773 --> 00:18:18,403
Hm? What was that?

338
00:18:21,433 --> 00:18:22,573
Nothing.

339
00:18:24,173 --> 00:18:25,513
I'm just telling you that...

340
00:18:26,343 --> 00:18:27,343
It's time

341
00:18:27,383 --> 00:18:29,473
I make you look this way.

342
00:18:42,033 --> 00:18:43,113
It's to your liking, right?

343
00:18:43,403 --> 00:18:44,403
It's delicious.

344
00:18:47,203 --> 00:18:48,123
Oh?

345
00:18:48,153 --> 00:18:49,193
Just the person I need.

346
00:18:49,953 --> 00:18:52,403
So tomorrow, I'm filming
a dance video at the hotel.

347
00:18:52,853 --> 00:18:54,093
Come give me a hand, would you?

348
00:18:55,933 --> 00:18:57,433
You should join me, Fu.

349
00:18:57,473 --> 00:18:58,473
It's gonna be great.

350
00:19:00,803 --> 00:19:01,803
But...

351
00:19:02,183 --> 00:19:03,393
I don't know how to dance.

352
00:19:03,723 --> 00:19:05,403
It's fine. I'll teach you.

353
00:19:06,183 --> 00:19:08,143
It's going to be absolutely viral,

354
00:19:08,343 --> 00:19:10,383
and even more people
will want to stay at this hotel

355
00:19:10,663 --> 00:19:13,183
when the hotel owner
is such a cutie.

356
00:19:14,353 --> 00:19:15,353
Am I right?

357
00:19:15,423 --> 00:19:16,453
Pretty please?

358
00:19:17,783 --> 00:19:18,583
Please...

359
00:19:18,703 --> 00:19:19,663
Alright, alright, alright.

360
00:19:19,703 --> 00:19:20,873
I'll give it a try.

361
00:19:21,973 --> 00:19:22,973
There we go.

362
00:19:23,663 --> 00:19:24,863
You're the cutest.

363
00:19:25,223 --> 00:19:27,823
Now I know what the vision
of new-generation hotel owners is like.

364
00:19:28,973 --> 00:19:29,973
I'll be waiting.

365
00:19:33,393 --> 00:19:36,223
You rotten banana!

366
00:19:36,873 --> 00:19:39,173
You and Kluayhom sure are
destined for each other.

367
00:19:40,413 --> 00:19:41,413
You tell me!

368
00:19:41,473 --> 00:19:43,703
He’s at your brother’s hotel
for a review right now.

369
00:19:44,333 --> 00:19:45,903
Been seducing him for real.

370
00:19:46,893 --> 00:19:49,693
Maybe he's gonna turn up
as your brother-in-law.

371
00:19:51,113 --> 00:19:52,383
So freaking extra.

372
00:19:53,113 --> 00:19:54,113
But it's a good thing.

373
00:19:54,323 --> 00:19:56,003
That way, my brother will leave you alone.

374
00:19:56,293 --> 00:19:58,113
But he's a horrible person.

375
00:19:58,762 --> 00:20:01,962
Do you want your brother
to end up with someone like that?

376
00:20:03,912 --> 00:20:05,172
Acting all like a well-wisher.

377
00:20:05,922 --> 00:20:06,852
You're just a dog in the manger.

378
00:20:06,892 --> 00:20:07,782
No!

379
00:20:07,822 --> 00:20:09,522
I'm with Moo on this.

380
00:20:09,562 --> 00:20:11,372
Don't let Fu be with Kluayhom.

381
00:20:11,612 --> 00:20:12,612
What?

382
00:20:12,732 --> 00:20:14,092
You too, Tian?

383
00:20:14,642 --> 00:20:15,642
Why not?

384
00:20:17,612 --> 00:20:18,982
What? Don't just ditch.

385
00:20:19,562 --> 00:20:20,932
Come back and tell us.

386
00:21:20,722 --> 00:21:22,022
(Self-Nurture)

387
00:22:00,982 --> 00:22:01,982
Wait.

388
00:22:04,172 --> 00:22:04,812
Here.

389
00:22:05,102 --> 00:22:06,572
New book, same cover.

390
00:22:09,592 --> 00:22:10,812
I said I didn't want it.

391
00:22:10,862 --> 00:22:12,272
This is not gonna be the same.

392
00:22:12,702 --> 00:22:13,702
I know.

393
00:22:17,352 --> 00:22:18,962
That's why I brought these tools.

394
00:22:19,622 --> 00:22:21,722
I asked a book repair shop,

395
00:22:22,182 --> 00:22:23,762
and they've taught me the basics.

396
00:22:23,942 --> 00:22:25,252
Let's repair it together.

397
00:22:26,042 --> 00:22:27,308
Do you have to go all those extra miles?

398
00:22:27,332 --> 00:22:28,332
What?

399
00:22:28,372 --> 00:22:30,772
I thought you said
your father gave it to you before he died.

400
00:22:31,052 --> 00:22:32,982
How dare you? My father is still alive!

401
00:22:35,332 --> 00:22:36,332
Oh...

402
00:22:37,672 --> 00:22:39,382
Just...

403
00:22:39,902 --> 00:22:40,902
forget about it.

404
00:22:42,342 --> 00:22:44,012
It'll never be the same.

405
00:22:44,742 --> 00:22:45,582
So...

406
00:22:45,622 --> 00:22:47,222
where is this new book you're giving me?

407
00:22:47,752 --> 00:22:48,752
Right.

408
00:22:50,592 --> 00:22:51,592
Here you go.

409
00:22:56,142 --> 00:22:57,272
Anything else?

410
00:23:00,202 --> 00:23:01,202
Not really.

411
00:23:15,103 --> 00:23:16,773
Okay. Let's start rehearsing.

412
00:23:17,053 --> 00:23:19,053
You record the video, silly Moo.

413
00:23:19,113 --> 00:23:20,313
- I'll leave it to you.
- Okay?

414
00:23:20,603 --> 00:23:22,333
So, to begin, our first move

415
00:23:22,373 --> 00:23:24,543
- is to hold up both fists.
- Hold them up like this?

416
00:23:24,633 --> 00:23:26,533
- Oh, um... bring them closer to you.
- Closer.

417
00:23:26,593 --> 00:23:27,829
You don't have to lean towards them.

418
00:23:27,853 --> 00:23:29,963
- Then jump in a circle.
- Jump.

419
00:23:30,513 --> 00:23:33,273
- Yes, jump. Like that. Yes.
- In a circle.

420
00:23:33,307 --> 00:23:34,727
Then we will...

421
00:23:34,761 --> 00:23:38,821
- tap, tap, tap on our chest.
- Tap, tap.

422
00:23:38,893 --> 00:23:41,173
Yeah, your arm should be
at that height. Good.

423
00:23:41,233 --> 00:23:43,328
Okay, then touch your head.

424
00:23:43,362 --> 00:23:44,922
Touch my head.

425
00:23:44,956 --> 00:23:47,536
- Then you thrust your hip.
- Thrust my hip...

426
00:23:47,673 --> 00:23:48,773
Twice. Bam! Bam!

427
00:23:48,807 --> 00:23:51,117
- One! Two!
- Or maybe like...

428
00:23:52,913 --> 00:23:53,913
What's the matter?

429
00:23:54,233 --> 00:23:56,093
Uh... I just got dizzy.

430
00:23:56,413 --> 00:23:57,593
I'll take a restroom break.

431
00:23:58,813 --> 00:23:59,813
Okay, go.

432
00:24:03,671 --> 00:24:05,491
- Hey... let's continue.
- Oh... yeah.

433
00:24:05,561 --> 00:24:06,811
- Right.
- So the next one...

434
00:24:31,861 --> 00:24:32,861
What's wrong?

435
00:24:34,101 --> 00:24:35,101
Nothing.

436
00:24:36,781 --> 00:24:37,811
Are you jealous?

437
00:24:41,001 --> 00:24:42,001
No.

438
00:24:43,721 --> 00:24:45,861
If you're jealous, just say it.

439
00:24:47,361 --> 00:24:49,301
Ugh, I said I wasn't!

440
00:25:01,961 --> 00:25:03,591
How can there be a guy like this?

441
00:25:03,701 --> 00:25:05,371
So adorable, even when he's mad.

442
00:25:09,196 --> 00:25:10,661
Oh... my poor heart is all melted.

443
00:25:11,536 --> 00:25:13,886
We're going to dance today.

444
00:25:14,436 --> 00:25:16,492
- We're dancing together, that's right.
- Dancing together?

445
00:25:16,516 --> 00:25:17,516
Are you ready?

446
00:25:17,856 --> 00:25:20,066
- I'm ready.
- Let's show them what we've got.

447
00:25:20,696 --> 00:25:21,756
Turn on the music!

448
00:25:24,916 --> 00:25:26,086
Okay, are you ready?

449
00:25:31,496 --> 00:25:32,496
Let's stretch first.

450
00:25:33,596 --> 00:25:34,596
Ready?

451
00:25:35,406 --> 00:25:37,236
Five, six, seven, eight...

452
00:25:44,506 --> 00:25:45,506
Now, spin.

453
00:25:52,676 --> 00:25:54,666
Turn off the music. Turn it off!

454
00:25:56,953 --> 00:25:58,223
Are you alright, Moo?

455
00:25:59,131 --> 00:26:00,351
Oh...

456
00:26:00,656 --> 00:26:02,816
I also want to dance.

457
00:26:03,596 --> 00:26:04,876
Is it okay if I join you?

458
00:26:04,916 --> 00:26:06,296
I also feel like dancing.

459
00:26:08,036 --> 00:26:09,856
You? Can you even dance, Moo?

460
00:26:09,946 --> 00:26:11,276
I don't think so.

461
00:26:11,956 --> 00:26:13,786
I'm craving some clout, too.

462
00:26:14,226 --> 00:26:15,856
I wanna join.

463
00:26:15,896 --> 00:26:17,776
The choreography doesn't seem that hard.

464
00:26:17,816 --> 00:26:18,866
Do me a favor, would you?

465
00:26:19,566 --> 00:26:20,896
Uh...

466
00:26:20,936 --> 00:26:22,376
Then who is going to hold the light?

467
00:26:23,236 --> 00:26:24,626
But I do think

468
00:26:24,696 --> 00:26:25,826
it's a great idea.

469
00:26:26,056 --> 00:26:27,406
With the three of us,

470
00:26:27,816 --> 00:26:29,036
it's going to be fun.

471
00:26:30,806 --> 00:26:31,806
Sure.

472
00:26:32,906 --> 00:26:33,706
Let's give it a try, then.

473
00:26:33,916 --> 00:26:35,616
Okay, everyone, let's dance.

474
00:26:35,686 --> 00:26:37,016
Music!

475
00:26:47,206 --> 00:26:49,296
Five, six, seven, eight...

476
00:26:57,556 --> 00:26:58,556
Meow...

477
00:26:58,836 --> 00:27:00,336
Mm-hm...

478
00:27:02,456 --> 00:27:03,726
A dog-sized cat.

479
00:27:34,406 --> 00:27:35,406
- Uh...
- I'm fine.

480
00:27:36,236 --> 00:27:37,236
It's hot here.

481
00:27:37,556 --> 00:27:39,172
I think that's enough exercise for today.

482
00:27:39,196 --> 00:27:41,566
Alright, everyone,
remember to come to Golden Peony Hotel.

483
00:27:41,666 --> 00:27:42,436
Bye-bye.

484
00:27:42,476 --> 00:27:43,606
Ugh, the light!

485
00:27:44,206 --> 00:27:45,566
The livestream is over!

486
00:27:46,066 --> 00:27:47,096
You, too!

487
00:27:47,136 --> 00:27:47,966
Turn off the light!

488
00:27:48,006 --> 00:27:49,656
Yes, I'll turn it off.

489
00:27:50,916 --> 00:27:52,086
Let me go already!

490
00:27:53,576 --> 00:27:54,576
I thought you liked it.

491
00:27:56,486 --> 00:27:57,486
You were lost in it.

492
00:28:37,766 --> 00:28:38,766
Why are you here?

493
00:28:38,946 --> 00:28:40,146
This is a staff-only zone.

494
00:28:42,426 --> 00:28:44,026
You're still into Fu, right?

495
00:28:46,646 --> 00:28:47,916
What are you saying?

496
00:28:49,276 --> 00:28:50,276
Let me rephrase.

497
00:28:51,056 --> 00:28:52,196
What is Fu

498
00:28:52,896 --> 00:28:54,316
to you?

499
00:28:56,476 --> 00:28:57,476
Well...

500
00:28:58,136 --> 00:28:59,436
he's my friend's brother.

501
00:29:03,136 --> 00:29:04,366
This BS again?

502
00:29:06,236 --> 00:29:08,176
I see you're still as irritating as ever.

503
00:29:14,986 --> 00:29:16,356
Don't ever let your guard down.

504
00:29:17,566 --> 00:29:19,126
He might still follow you around today,

505
00:29:20,606 --> 00:29:22,606
but it's not like
he would keep doing this forever.

506
00:29:24,796 --> 00:29:26,136
Stop being so selfish.

507
00:29:48,576 --> 00:29:49,576
Fu...

508
00:29:55,856 --> 00:29:57,396
Don't say those things to Moo.

509
00:29:58,716 --> 00:30:00,116
I'm the one pursuing him.

510
00:30:00,516 --> 00:30:02,036
He didn't have anything to do with it.

511
00:30:07,476 --> 00:30:08,476
Fu,

512
00:30:09,596 --> 00:30:11,436
so you chase after him

513
00:30:12,966 --> 00:30:15,166
even when he doesn't see your worth at all?

514
00:30:17,046 --> 00:30:18,046
And this

515
00:30:18,736 --> 00:30:20,676
is not your concern at all, Kluayhom.

516
00:30:21,216 --> 00:30:22,216
It is.

517
00:30:23,356 --> 00:30:24,726
Because I like you!

518
00:30:25,606 --> 00:30:26,846
I've liked you for a long time,

519
00:30:27,106 --> 00:30:28,236
ever since we were little!

520
00:30:30,596 --> 00:30:31,636
And where did that get me?

521
00:30:32,066 --> 00:30:33,166
You only care for Moo.

522
00:30:33,386 --> 00:30:34,666
You only have your eyes for him.

523
00:30:42,336 --> 00:30:43,336
Fu...

524
00:30:49,516 --> 00:30:50,756
Be honest with me.

525
00:30:54,695 --> 00:30:56,625
For once, can you give me a chance?

526
00:31:00,136 --> 00:31:01,136
Please?

527
00:31:02,778 --> 00:31:04,228
Just once?

528
00:31:09,246 --> 00:31:10,246
Then...

529
00:31:11,876 --> 00:31:13,716
Would you come meet me at my room tonight?

530
00:31:32,116 --> 00:31:33,796
Why did you invite me
out here for a drink?

531
00:31:34,036 --> 00:31:35,596
Someone broke your heart, Fu?

532
00:31:37,306 --> 00:31:38,306
Not yet.

533
00:31:41,666 --> 00:31:42,896
But I don't know.

534
00:31:47,816 --> 00:31:48,916
Is it about Moo?

535
00:31:49,265 --> 00:31:50,265
Tai,

536
00:31:51,036 --> 00:31:52,366
how am I not good enough?

537
00:31:55,326 --> 00:31:56,736
I'm hot

538
00:31:56,779 --> 00:31:58,084
and cool,

539
00:31:58,656 --> 00:32:00,256
with plenty of money to splurge.

540
00:32:01,966 --> 00:32:05,266
I've been pursuing him for so long,

541
00:32:06,256 --> 00:32:08,716
so how come he never seems to cave in?

542
00:32:10,236 --> 00:32:11,276
If he were a rock,

543
00:32:11,946 --> 00:32:13,646
with this constant rain dripping on him,

544
00:32:14,286 --> 00:32:15,086
jeez,

545
00:32:15,266 --> 00:32:16,766
he'd be so porous by now.

546
00:32:23,003 --> 00:32:24,003
I know

547
00:32:26,056 --> 00:32:27,916
that he never looks at me,

548
00:32:29,696 --> 00:32:31,366
but I've always been trying.

549
00:32:34,106 --> 00:32:35,106
Though right now,

550
00:32:36,716 --> 00:32:38,376
I'm not so sure

551
00:32:41,296 --> 00:32:43,826
if not moving on from Moo

552
00:32:45,276 --> 00:32:48,006
is making him
more uncomfortable than anything else.

553
00:32:49,816 --> 00:32:51,216
So I'm thinking...

554
00:32:55,006 --> 00:32:56,876
if I should start over.

555
00:33:26,016 --> 00:33:27,366
